From 34ee95e35fb7c997db05a1012fcadfe681bdbd69 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rishi <rishi@market-cockpit.local>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 16:48:09 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(news): exposure weighting + economic capture + duration
 + losers + small/mid caps
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 0082 — addresses institutional review: "AMD/AVGO/MRVL/AMZN/GOOG
treated equally — basket dilution. Need exposure weighting, economic
capture, duration, structural losers, small/mid caps".

5 NEW DIMENSIONS PER BENEFICIARY

1. EXPOSURE_INTENSITY — DIRECT (95) / STRONG (78) / MEDIUM (55)
   / INDIRECT (35) / STRATEGIC (20). Drives card colour + score weight.

2. ECONOMIC_CAPTURE — MASSIVE (95) / HIGH (75) / MODERATE (50)
   / MARGINAL (25) / STRATEGIC_ONLY (10). Separates narrative from
   real margin/revenue capture (AMZN/GOOG TPU = STRATEGIC_ONLY since
   internal-only; SK Hynix HBM = MASSIVE since external + pricing power).

3. SIZE_CLASS — LARGE_CAP / MID_CAP / SMALL_CAP for size-tilt filter.

4. DURATION per adaptation:
   MULTI_YEAR_STRUCTURAL — ALT_ACCELERATOR, AI_NETWORKING, MEMORY_HIERARCHY, LIQUID_COOLING
   SECULAR              — POWER_EFFICIENCY, EDGE_INFERENCE, SOFTWARE_ORCHESTRATION
   POLICY_SENSITIVE     — BEHIND_THE_METER (depends on grid policy / IRA)

5. STRUCTURAL_LOSERS per adaptation:
   POWER_EFFICIENCY      → INTC (HIGH), DELL (MEDIUM)
   ALT_ACCELERATOR       → NVDA (LOW share-of-wallet), INTC (MEDIUM)
   EDGE_INFERENCE        → CDW
   BEHIND_THE_METER      → EXC, AEP (T&D bypass)
   SOFTWARE_ORCHESTRATION→ IBM, ORCL legacy
   AI_NETWORKING         → CSCO, JNPR (legacy enterprise)
   MEMORY_HIERARCHY      → STX, WDC (HDD-heavy)

SMALL/MID CAP ADDITIONS (4 per adaptation, 32 total)
   POWER_EFFICIENCY:      MPWR, POWI, LSCC, SITM
   ALT_ACCELERATOR:       ALAB, CRDO, AEHR, CAMT
   EDGE_INFERENCE:        CCOI, DBX, VTEX, WIX
   BEHIND_THE_METER:      EOSE, FCEL, NNE, CGRN
   SOFTWARE_ORCHESTRATION:DT, FROG, GTLB, CFLT
   AI_NETWORKING:         ALAB, CRDO, CALX, EXTR
   MEMORY_HIERARCHY:      ONTO, CAMT, ACMR, ALAB
   LIQUID_COOLING:        FIX, MOD, AAON, EMR

Each ticker has hand-curated metadata (exposure, capture, size, rationale)
in seed_metadata. Tickers learned dynamically from articles get conservative
defaults (INDIRECT/MARGINAL/MID_CAP) until rationale is added.

CAUSAL RELEVANCE FILTER (the Dua-Lipa fix)
recordBeneficiary now requires the article's primary_node to be in the
adaptation's triggered_by list. SemiAnalysis HBM4 article (primary_node
MEMORY_INFRA) → counts toward MEMORY_HIERARCHY + ALT_ACCELERATOR (both
triggered by MEMORY_INFRA). Dua Lipa Samsung suit (primary_node = NONE
or unrelated) → no adaptations counted. Eliminates ontology contamination.

COMPOSITE SCORE for ranking
  composite = 0.5 × exposure + 0.3 × capture + 0.2 × accumulated
  Caps accumulated at 50 so a few mentions don't outrank seed quality.
  DIRECT / MASSIVE seeds always rank above weakly-accumulated INDIRECTs.

UI
- Each beneficiary chip color-coded by exposure (green=DIRECT,
  cyan=STRONG, amber=MEDIUM, gray=INDIRECT/STRATEGIC)
- Composite score shown on chip
- Size suffix (s = small cap, m = mid cap, large = no marker)
- Tooltip: full rationale + exposure/capture/size scores
- Duration badge per adaptation (MULTI-YEAR STRUCTURAL / SECULAR / etc.)
- Structural losers row with severity (H/M/L)

KV key bumped beneficiary:adapt:v1: → v2: to clear pre-filter polluted
ledger. Cache key v28 → v29. tsc clean.
